data.description: For the first time in 33 years, this beguiling 4 bedroom, 4.5 bath stucco house located on sought after River Hill Road is coming on the market. A charming limestone entrance leads into a dramatic two-story vaulted great room with French brushed lacquered walls which directs the eye to the impressive working fireplace. Also, on the first floor are the primary bedroom, two full baths, an inviting dining room with fireplace, and a charming eat in kitchen. The elegant library with its bar, handsome built-in bookcases framing the custom designed fireplace opens onto the stunning terrace set in a lush and very private garden. The second floor has three well-proportioned bedrooms and two full baths. One of the bedrooms has a balcony overlooking the great room. The unfinished basement, which has great potential for expansion, contains the laundry, a half bath, and a playroom well loved by teenagers & a 2+ car garage.  Exclusions: Hand-painted canvas wallpaper Mural in hall from Dining Room to Library; Library Clock; Woman Ship Figurehead over entry in Great Room; Leather Screen in Dining Room; Hall Clock & Shelf; Linen fold panel over great room front window.
